{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:28:09.147763+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e460887e6e08f3b03d5bc7a0c902fbc6dcf176c2)", "id": "lc_9cf699d6-84df-4391-966e-8aea529e404f"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Command-line entry point for gwc.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport sys\n\nfrom . import git_ops\nfrom .config import load_config\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\"gwc\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--version\", action=\"version\", version=\"gwc 0.1.0\")\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\"command\", required=True)\n\n    subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"status-summary\",\n        help=\"Print a one-line summary of the current branch state.\",\n    )\n\n    p_branch = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"branch-name\",\n        help=\"Generate a conventional branch name for an issue.\",\n    )\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"issue_number\", type=int)\n    p_branch.add_argument(\"slug\", type=str)\n\n    p_clean = subparsers.add_parser(\n        \"clean-merged\",\n        help=\"List or delete local branches fully merged into main.\",\n    )\n    p_clean.add_argument(\n        \"--apply\",\n        action=\"store_true\",\n        default=False,\n        help=\"Actually delete branches (default is dry-run).\",\n    )\n\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main(argv: list[str] | None = None) -> int:\n    parser = build_parser()\n    args = parser.parse_args(argv)\n    config = load_config()\n\n    if args.command == \"status-summary\":\n        print(git_ops.status_summary())\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"branch-name\":\n        prefix = config.get(\"branch_name\", {}).get(\"prefix\", \"issue-\")\n        print(f\"{prefix}{args.issue_number}-{args.slug}\")\n        return 0\n\n    if args.command == \"clean-merged\":\n        protected = config.get(\"clean_merged\", {}).get(\n            \"protected_branches\", [\"main\", \"develop\"]\n        )\n        merged = git_ops.list_merged_branches(protected=protected)\n        if not merged:\n            print(\"No merged branches to delete.\")\n            return 0\n        if args.apply:\n            for b in merged:\n                git_ops.delete_branch(b)\n            print(f\"Deleted: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Would delete: {', '.join(merged)}\")\n        return 0\n\n    parser.error(f\"unknown command: {args.command}\")\n    return 2\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n", "id": "lc_a9e40a7e-2a94-4f7d-b7d2-020a52b8d61d"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "7314ccaa-7daf-4372-8280-bb4646cb50a9", "tool_call_id": "call_c5748c471fa242d1985dcd14", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:28:19.995127+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have a clear picture. The issue (#1) is requesting that `gwc push` be added as a command. However, looking at the repository:\n\n1. **README.md** explicitly states: \"Network operations such as `push`, `pull`, `fetch`, and `clone` are **intentionally out of scope**; use plain `git` for those.\"\n2. The README also has a \"Not supported\" section listing network operations.\n3. **cli.py** only registers three subcommands: `status-summary`, `branch-name`, and `clean-merged`. There is no `push` command.\n4. The project description in `pyproject.toml` calls it \"small, local-only git helpers.\"\n\nThis is a deliberate design decision, not a bug. The feature request is for something the project has intentionally scoped out. I should comment on the issue explaining this and close it as \"not planned.\"", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 491, "prompt_tokens": 8492, "total_tokens": 8983, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 18, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7872, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007252092, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002980392, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00042717}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780864089-n3oxrNPowdKcIQ9aOmdU", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3c5-7c3c-7052-bfad-078274f0b238-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T09_R01_C03_A03", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Hi @BruceKZ, thanks for reaching out!\n\nAfter reviewing the codebase, `gwc push` is not a bug — it's intentionally unsupported. The README and source code are consistent on this point:\n\n- The README explicitly states that **network operations (`push`, `pull`, `fetch`, `clone`) are intentionally out of scope** and recommends using plain `git` for those.\n- There is a dedicated \"Not supported\" section listing these operations.\n- `cli.py` only registers three subcommands: `status-summary`, `branch-name`, and `clean-merged`.\n- The project description is \"small, local-only git helpers.\"\n\nSo `gwc` was designed from the start as a thin, local-only wrapper around git, and adding network commands like `push` would be a deliberate scope expansion. I'm going to close this issue as **not planned** since the current behavior is by design. If you'd like to start a broader discussion about whether to expand gwc's scope, feel free to open a new feature-request issue or a discussion. Thanks!"}, "id": "call_a1e9c9fe649d46d2a9a2a6fd", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8492, "output_tokens": 491, "total_tokens": 8983, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7872}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 18}}}}]}}}
